M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[ps, behavioral, framing, system1, bias, lever, debiasing, skills]
M||vari|A — Lean Protocol
M||purp|Fast psychological reasoning for hi-frequency br cn
M||bran|nz, hb (and future sub-brands)
M||auto|BRAND_MEMORY.md + STRATEGY_LOG.md + LEVER_TRACKER.md before every sn
M||trig|[cp audit, framing check, sy 1 filter, lever selection, quick ps rv, sl post, pd cp, ad cp, em cp]
M||outp|[A/B variants w/ named levers, st log entry, LEVER_TRACKER up, BRAND_MEMORY append]
M||call|[principles.md, tools.md, BRAND_MEMORY.md, STRATEGY_LOG.md, LEVER_TRACKER.md]
M||sour|principles.md v1.0 — if cn diverges, principles.md is canonical. Run skills-sync after any edit to principles.md.
M||tx|---
M|CONS|tx|> Fast activation. Sharp output. Built for sl posts, pd cp,
M|CONS|tx|> quick cg decisions, and any cn needed w/o a long sn.
M|CONS|tx|> Claude reasons quickly but never skips the br intake or feedback loop.
M|CONS|tx|---
M|STEP|Befo|
M|STEP|tx|1. Read `BRAND_MEMORY.md` for the relevant br
M|STEP|tx|2. Read `STRATEGY_LOG.md` — find the last 3 entries for this surface tp
M|STEP|tx|3. Check `LEVER_TRACKER.md` — is any lever at Triple Cap (used 3x in a row)?
M|STEP|tx|4. Run the Pre-cn Checklist (Step 1)
M|STEP|tx|If br memory file does not exist → STOP. Ask Stark to fill it before proceeding.
M|STEP|tx|Never work anonymously. Never assume br context.
M|STEP|tx|---
M|STEP|tx|> Run this AFTER loading br context (Step 0). Answer before selecting any layer.
M|STEP|tx|> This is kh's core framework — every piece of cn targets one sy primarily.
M|STEP|**An|**
M|STEP|tx|\| Question \| sy 1 \| sy 2 \|
M|STEP|tx|\|---\|---\|---\|
M|STEP|tx|\| Speed of audience decision \| Instant — gut, scroll-stop, emotional \| Deliberate — comparing, researching, justifying \|
M|STEP|tx|\| cn goal \| Stop the scroll, cr feeling, bd desire \| Explain, convince, resolve objection \|
M|STEP|tx|\| Funnel stage \| Discovery, awareness, re-engagement \| Consideration, decision, post-purchase \|
M|STEP|rt|**
M|STEP|it|**sy 1 cn** → Lead w/ L1 (Perception), L2 (Desire), L6 (Attention/Spread)
M|STEP|it|**sy 2 cn** → Lead w/ L3 (Influence/Persuasion), L4 (Behavioral Economics)
M|STEP|it|**sy 1 → sy 2 transition** (moving someone from scroll to decision) → L2 + L3 bridge
M|STEP|tx|State your rt before proceeding to Step 1. Do not skip.
M|STEP|tx|---
M|STEP|Answ|
M|STEP|tx|\| Question \| Answer \|
M|STEP|tx|\|---\|---\|
M|STEP|tx|\| Which br? \| \|
M|STEP|tx|\| Which surface? (sl / website / pd / em / ad / cg) \| \|
M|STEP|tx|\| cn goal? (acquire / retain / deepen loyalty) \| \|
M|STEP|tx|\| Is this sy 1 cn? (gut-feel, scroll-stop, instant emotion) \| \|
M|STEP|tx|\| Or sy 2? (deliberate, considered, research-mode) \| \|
M|STEP|tx|\| sl signal or self-signal? (showing others vs validating self) \| \|
M|STEP|tx|\| br lifecycle stage? (0→1 / growing / scaling / repositioning) \| \|
M|STEP|tx|\| Any lever at Triple Cap right now? \| \|
M|STEP|tx|---
M|STEP|tx|Read the last 3 STRATEGY_LOG entries for this br + surface.
M|STEP|**If|**
M|STEP|it|Did it work? (check Results field)
M|STEP|it|YES → identify the mechanism, evolve it, check Triple Cap
M|STEP|it|NO → diagnose why (wrong lever? wrong surface? wrong timing?), select new lever
M|STEP|it|pnd → note it, proceed w/ new cn, flag that results are still outstanding
M|STEP|**If|**
M|STEP|it|Fresh start. Full layer reasoning below.
M|STEP|**Tr|**
M|STEP|tx|If the same psychological lever has been the PRIMARY driver 3 consecutive times
M|STEP|tx|for the same br surface → it is CAPPED. Select a different lever.
M|STEP|tx|Claude must not override this rule even if the lever is performing well.
M|STEP|tx|Variety maintains psychological freshness in the audience's mind.
M|STEP|tx|---
M|STEP|tx|Claude activates the most relevant 2-3 layers per piece of cn.
M|STEP|tx|Not all layers fire every time. Choose based on surface + goal.
M|STEP|tx|---
M|L1 —|*Act|website cp, pd pages, first-touch sl cn, ad*
M|L1 —|**Co|** The brain decides in milliseconds. Before logic fires,
M|L1 —|tx|the subconscious has already judged. cn must pass this filter first.
M|L1 —|**Ke|**
M|L1 —|it|Processing fluency — easier to process = more trusted. Simplicity signals qual.
M|L1 —|it|Halo effect — one strong positive cue colors everything else
M|L1 —|it|Thin-slicing — people form accurate impressions from tiny amounts of information
M|L1 —|it|Pattern interrupt — break expected format to force attention
M|L1 —|**Ac|** Ask — *what does someone feel in the first 2 seconds?*
M|L1 —|tx|If the answer is "nothing" — this layer needs work before anything else.
M|L1 —|**Re|** Search current examples of brands in this
M|L1 —|tx|category using silence, minimalism, or visual contrast as perception tools.
M|L1 —|tx|---
M|L2 —|*Act|pd descriptions, cg hooks, br storytelling*
M|L2 —|**Co|** People don't buy pd. They buy who they want to become.
M|L2 —|tx|The gap btw current self and aspirational self is the engine of desire.
M|L2 —|**Ke|**
M|L2 —|it|Jobs-to-be-Done — what progress is the cs trying to make in their life?
M|L2 —|it|Identity-based desire — "people like me wear/use/buy this"
M|L2 —|it|Aspirational self gap — show the future version, not the current pd
M|L2 —|it|Authenticity signal — desire built on false promises collapses; on truth, compounds
M|L2 —|**Ac|** Ask — *who does the cs become after buying this?*
M|L2 —|tx|That answer is the cn. The pd is just the vehicle.
M|L2 —|**Re|** Search how small independent brands in this
M|L2 —|tx|category have used founder story or cs transformation as their primary hook.
M|L2 —|tx|---
M|L3 —|*Act|CTAs, launch cn, limited releases, sl proof moments*
M|L3 —|**Ci|**
M|L3 —|tx|\| Principle \| When to use \| When NOT to use \|
M|L3 —|tx|\|---\|---\|---\|
M|L3 —|tx|\| Reciprocity \| Give value before asking \| Don't force it — feels transactional \|
M|L3 —|tx|\| Commitment \| Post-purchase loyalty cn \| Early acquisition — too soon \|
M|L3 —|tx|\| sl proof \| Mid-funnel, consideration stage \| br new launches — no proof yet \|
M|L3 —|tx|\| Authority \| tc or qual claims \| Casual/lifestyle cn — kills vibe \|
M|L3 —|tx|\| Liking \| br voice, community cn \| Hard sell moments \|
M|L3 —|tx|\| Scarcity \| Drops, limited editions, deadlines \| Everyday pd — loses meaning \|
M|L3 —|tx|\| Unity \| Community, shared identity cn \| Broad audiences — too generic \|
M|L3 —|**Ac|** Ask — *which principle is this cn trying to activate?*
M|L3 —|tx|Never activate more than 2 simultaneously — audiences feel manipulated.
M|L3 —|tx|---
M|L4 —|*Act|pricing cn, pd tiers, checkout exp, offer framing*
M|L4 —|**Ke|**
M|L4 —|it|Loss aversion — "don't miss" outperforms "you'll gain" by ~2x
M|L4 —|it|Anchoring — first price/value seen sets the reference frame for everything after
M|L4 —|it|Decoy effect — 3-tier pricing makes the middle tier feel like the smart choice
M|L4 —|it|Paradox of choice — fewer options = higher conversion
M|L4 —|it|Peak-end rule — people remember the peak moment and the ending, not the average
M|L4 —|**Ac|** Ask — *is this cn abt a decision?*
M|L4 —|tx|If yes, frame around what they lose by not acting, not what they gain by acting.
M|L4 —|tx|---
M|L5 —|*Act|br identity cn, visual direction, cg naming, tone*
M|L5 —|**Ke|**
M|L5 —|it|Mental availability (Byron Sharp) — be thought of first in the buying moment
M|L5 —|it|Distinctive assets — one repeatable visual/verbal signature beats many varied ones
M|L5 —|it|Emotional encoding — stories are remembered; specs are forgotten
M|L5 —|it|Archetype alignment — br personality shd map to one Jungian archetype
M|L5 —|tx|consistently (Rebel, Creator, Lover, Hero, Sage, Innocent, Explorer, Ruler)
M|L5 —|**Ac|** Ask — *if someone saw this w/ no logo, wld they know
M|L5 —|tx|it was this br?* If no — this layer needs work.
M|L5 —|tx|---
M|L6 —|*Act|sl cn, hooks, viral mechanics, cg structure*
M|L6 —|**Ke|**
M|L6 —|it|Curiosity gap — open a loop the audience needs to close ("here's what we found...")
M|L6 —|it|Zeigarnik effect — unfinished things are remembered (never complete the story in post 1)
M|L6 —|it|Von Restorff — the thing that's different gets remembered
M|L6 —|it|Emotional contagion — hi-arousal emotions (awe, excitement, outrage) spread 3x more
M|L6 —|it|Pattern interrupt — break the expected format in the first 2 seconds
M|L6 —|**Ac|** Ask — *why wld someone share this?*
M|L6 —|tx|If there's no answer — it won't spread regardless of qual.
M|L6 —|**Re|** Search recent examples of small brands
M|L6 —|tx|that generated outsized reach w/ minimal spend. Extract the mechanism, not the execution.
M|L6 —|tx|---
M|L7 —|*Act|community cn, br positioning, cultural moments, identity cg*
M|L7 —|**Ke|**
M|L7 —|it|In-group/out-group — belonging to "us" requires knowing who "them" is
M|L7 —|it|Tribal identity signals — language, aesthetics, and references that mark membership
M|L7 —|it|Status signaling — in fashion specifically, pd signal aspiration hierarchy
M|L7 —|it|Cultural congruence — cn that feels out of sync w/ current cultural moment fails
M|L7 —|tx|regardless of psychological soundness
M|L7 —|**Ac|** Ask — *what group does this cn make someone feel part of?*
M|L7 —|tx|And — *is that the group this br is building?*
M|L7 —|**Ti|** When cn is delivered matters as much as what it says.
M|L7 —|tx|A launch post, a mid-scroll organic post, and a retargeting touchpoint are
M|L7 —|tx|psychologically different events requiring different lever activation.
M|L7 —|tx|---
M|STEP|tx|Always produce exactly 2 variants. Each tests a DIFFERENT psychological lever.
M|STEP|tx|Never produce 2 variants that are just tonal rewrites of the same lever.
M|STEP|**Va|**
M|STEP|- Pr|[state which layer and which principle]
M|STEP|- Ra|[one sentence — why this lever for this br at this stage]
M|STEP|- Co|[the actual output]
M|STEP|**Va|**
M|STEP|- Pr|[state which layer and which principle]
M|STEP|- Ra|[one sentence — why this is a meaningfully different psychological tst]
M|STEP|- Co|[the actual output]
M|STEP|**Ru|** [Which to run first and why — based on br lifecycle stage
M|STEP|tx|and what's been tried before per st Log]
M|STEP|tx|---
M|STEP|Befo|
M|STEP|it|[ ] Does this pass the 2-second sy 1 filter?
M|STEP|it|[ ] Is the psychological lever intentional and named?
M|STEP|it|[ ] Is it consistent w/ br Memory File?
M|STEP|it|[ ] Does it serve the br's desired perception — not undermine it?
M|STEP|it|[ ] Is the Triple Cap Rule respected?
M|STEP|it|[ ] Are both variants testing genuinely different levers?
M|STEP|tx|If any box fails — revise before delivering.
M|STEP|tx|---
