M|6D —|tx|```
M|6D —|tx|After all writes → if previous cycle Results field is filled → run `@kh results` to trigger proposal.
M|6D —|tx|---
M|RESE|When|
M|RESE|tx|1. Search for current real-world br examples (not older than 18 months)
M|RESE|tx|2. Find both large AND small br examples — weight small brands equally
M|RESE|3. E|what happened → what psychological mechanism drove it →
M|RESE|tx|what wld need to be true for it to work for this br
M|RESE|tx|4. Never reference examples directly in output ("like X did") —
M|RESE|tx|extract the mechanism and apply it natively
M|RESE|tx|5. Discard examples that don't have a clear psychological mechanism behind them
M|RESE|tx|---
M|TRIP|tx|The same psychological lever cannot be the PRIMARY driver for more than
M|TRIP|tx|3 consecutive pieces of cn on the same br surface.
M|TRIP|tx|Tracking lives in `LEVER_TRACKER.md` per br per surface.
M|TRIP|**Wh|**
M|TRIP|tx|Audiences psychologically adapt. A lever that worked 3 times will produce
M|TRIP|tx|diminishing returns on the 4th. The br's cn starts feeling predictable.
M|TRIP|tx|Predictable = invisible. Invisible = no impact.
M|TRIP|**Wh|**
M|TRIP|tx|Same Cialdini principle, same layer, same core psychological mechanism.
M|TRIP|tx|Evolving the execution (different cp, different visual) does NOT reset the cap.
M|TRIP|tx|Only switching the PRIMARY lever resets it.
M|TRIP|**Ca|**
M|TRIP|tx|After using a different primary lever once, the previous lever's cap resets.
M|TRIP|tx|---
M|TRIP|tx|*Variant A is optimized for speed. When a task requires full st depth,
M|TRIP|tx|cg architecture, or br repositioning — use 02-kh.md instead.*
M|TRIP|tx|---
M|LEAR|tx|> kh appends one line here after each sn when results are confirmed (not pnd).
M|LEAR|tx|> Over time this builds br-specific psychological intelligence. Do not edit manually.
